cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to image deformation, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of optical flow theory and approximation theory also suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics).
